ocesses and the benefits that attended the incorporation of feminism into the frames of economic and racial justice, individual rights, and Christian values. It thus illuminates both the reach and the staying power of second-wave feminism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFeminismzUnited States. 0aLiberalismzUnited States. 0aWomen in public lifezUnited States. 0aWomen's rightszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh1 aManiates, Maria Rika.1 aPalisca, Claude V., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311053801440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014393540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300143935423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300143935/original  a978-3-11-053801-4  Yale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles